branch r42linuxbuild


IfcPLusPlus
============
open source software to view ifc-files on Linux
https://github.com/berndhahnebach/IfcPlusPlus

The Repository is based on the work done by Fabian Gerold 
http://code.google.com/p/ifcplusplus/

The cmake files and some bug fixes are taken form Sylvian Marie from VTREEM
https://github.com/VTREEM/IFCPlusPlus/

Find a forum thread about this Linux build at
http://www.forum.freecadweb.org/viewtopic.php?f=23&t=5101


Packagelist
===========
$ apt-get install cmake git 
$ apt-get install libboost-dev libopenscenegraph-dev libqt4-dev

Internal Carve of IfcPlusPlus is used.


IfcPLusPlus
===========
get source code, change branch and build
$ git clone git://github.com/berndhahnebach/IfcPlusPlus/   ifcplusplus-code
$ cd ifcplusplus-code
$ git checkout r42linuxbuild
$ mkdir build
$ cd build
You need to tell IfcPLusPlus where your Carve is. Since CMakeLists.txt is optimized for use of external Carve
I had to set Carvedirectories even for internal Carve. In my case it was:
$ cmake \
-D CARVE_SOURCE_DIR=/home/hugo/Documents/projekte--ifc/ifcplusplus/ifcplusplus-code/Carve   \
-D CARVE_BINARY_DIR=/home/hugo/Documents/projekte--ifc/ifcplusplus/ifcplusplus-code/build   \
../
$ make
$ cd Release
$ ./IfcPlusPlusViewer

Yeah, it runs on Linux !!!

